WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
These are the AI Powered Coding Assistants that you should know about.

00:00:02.800 --> 00:00:03.800
First up is Curser.

00:00:03.800 --> 00:00:07.480
Curser is like VS Code, but rebuilt from the ground up with AI in mind.

00:00:07.480 --> 00:00:10.640
It's designed so that you can talk to your codebase directly, generate new files, and

00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:13.320
even refactor entire projects with natural language.

00:00:13.320 --> 00:00:15.800
Next up is Positron Assistant, built right into Positron.

00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:19.740
Positron Assistant is tuned for data science, dashboard, and Python app workflows.

00:00:19.740 --> 00:00:23.280
You can ask it to write code, explain errors, or even create a shiny or streamlined app

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:25.240
all from scratch without leaving your IDE.

00:00:25.240 --> 00:00:26.240
Next up is Windsurf.

00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:30.160
Windsurf is an AI-first IDE with focus on agentic workflows, meaning it can actually

00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:32.320
plan and execute coding tasks for you.

00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:35.720
And lastly, GitHub Copilot is the OG AI Coding Assistant.

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:39.020
Copilot lives inside of your editor and predicts what you're trying to code before you even

00:00:39.020 --> 00:00:40.020
finish typing.

00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:43.480
Perfect for generating boilerplate, filling in function logic, or speeding up the repetitive

00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:44.480
coding tasks.

00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:46.919
Make sure you leave any questions in the comments below and follow along for more data science

00:00:46.919 --> 00:00:47.919
content.

00:00:47.919 --> 00:00:47.919


